Introduction

Kim Ah-young, more popularly known as Yura, is a South Korean singer, rapper, artist, actress, and variety star under Awesome ENT. She is best known for being the member, Main Rapper, Lead Dancer, Vocalist, and Visual of the South Korean pop girl group Girl's Day under DreamT Entertainment.

Yura along with Hyeri, joined the South Korean pop girl group Girl's Day in September 2010 after the departures of members Jisun and Jang Hyeri (known as Ji In at the time). Her first release with the group was the digital single "Girl's Day Party #2" released on the 29th of October 2010.

After leaving DreamT Entertainment on the 11th of January 2019 due to deciding not to renew her contract, Yura has since starred in dramas such as "Now, We Are Breaking Up" and "Forecasting Love and Weather". On the 20th of March 2019, it was announced that Yura had signed a contract with Awesome ENT.

On the 22nd of September 2020, Yura announced she would be opening her personal art gallery, Yul Land with her first expedition being held from the 12th-15th of October 2020.
